cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.CV, cs.GR

Reasoning: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning to train level-designing agents. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to generate game content. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses framing level design as a game and using reinforcement learning to optimize the final level quality. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss the use of computer vision techniques in the game environments. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also less likely but possible as the paper may discuss the visual aspects of the generated game content.
